
/*
 * This Hyperlambda code snippet adds nodes retrieved from the [.arguments] node to a specific location in the node hierarchy. The [add] slot inserts nodes at the path specified by its expression, while [get-nodes] fetches nodes from the [.arguments] node. The operation effectively appends argument nodes to the "where" clause of a data reading operation. 
 * 
 * 1. [add] - Inserts nodes at the specified location in the node hierarchy.
 * 2. [get-nodes] - Retrieves nodes from the [.arguments] node to be added.
 */
add:x:./*/data.read/*/where/*
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*
